item.title: Need Development team!
item.dc:creator: @xx_qwertyuiop_xx xx qwertyuiop xx
item.description:
@xx_qwertyuiop_xx wrote:

Lookie here, I found some variables while screwing around in a client.
Use these.

anInt61 = npc combat
anInt157 = item id
anInt174 = item model id
anInt181 = item size / 100
anInt190 = y rotation
anInt198 = x rotation
anInt204 = unknown
anInt169 = zoom offset x
anInt194 = zoom offset y
anInt165 = male model id
anInt188 = male sleeve model id
anInt200 = female model id
anInt164 = female sleeve model id
anInt185 = male forearm model id
anInt162 = female forearm model id
anInt175 = male chat interface model id
anInt166 = male face model?
anInt197 = female chat interface model id
anInt173 = another male face model id?
anInt232 = colour of interface writing
anInt233 = weapon on interface size
anInt234 = weapon on interface id
anInt754 = object id
anInt822 = ignore list length
anInt836 = npc count
anInt857 = interface id
anInt863 = playerrights
anInt877 = npc id
anInt891 = player count
anInt899 = Number of people on friends list
anInt902 = scrollbar border color
anInt918 = height
anInt927 = Scrollbar border color
anInt958 = port offset
anInt1006 = how many days ago you last logged in
anInt1008 = frame
anInt1034 = x coord
anInt1035 = y coord
anInt1054 = flashing sidebar
anInt1069 = map region X
anInt1070 = map region Y
anInt1120 = members/free - 0 for members, 1 for free
anInt1137 = spell id 
anInt1154 = number of unread messages
anInt1167 = members(201),free(200)
anInt1216 = typing field (username or password, and in my case server ip and port =P)
anInt1221 = sidebar
anInt1225 = interface over chat
anInt1276 = interface over chat
anInt1287 = public chat mode
anInt1287 = private chat mode
anInt1406 = current offset for stream
anInt1502 = index id of direction player is facing, <32768 = npc, >32768 = player
anInt1533 = player current health
anInt1534 = player max health
anInt1535 = player chat text size
anInt1538 = player direction x coord
anInt1539 = player direction y coord
anInt1705 = your combat level

I’m not registering, but I wish you luck with your project.
